## 2. GitHub Repository Structure

The user's knowledge base will be a private GitHub repository with the following structure:

```text
/
├── raw/                # Source files (PDF, MD, TXT, etc.)
│   └── research_paper_v1.pdf
├── wiki/               # The Primary Database (Markdown)
│   ├── index.md        # Entry point for LLM/User
│   ├── log.md          # Chronological record
│   ├── entities/       # People, places, organizations
│   ├── concepts/       # Theories, ideas
│   └── topics/         # Broad subject areas
├── schema/             # System Instructions (Immutable-ish)
│   ├── AGENTS.md       # Agent definitions & personas
│   └── WORKFLOWS.md    # Ingest, Lint, Query protocols
└── memvid/             # Session Memory (.json / .mv2)
    └── session-2024-04-07.json
```

