## 4. Rust Crate & Module Design

### `core` (WASM Binary)
- `lib.rs`: `wasm_bindgen` exports for the JS bridge.
- `app.rs`: State machine to manage the current session.
- `error.rs`: Custom error types for WASM/Async boundaries.

### `agents`
- `trait Agent`: Defines `run()` and `context` requirements.
- `ingest.rs`: Processes raw files → Wiki pages.
- `maintainer.rs`: Synchronizes multi-page updates.
- `lint.rs`: Scans for orphans/contradictions.

### `github`
- `client.rs`: Async HTTP client for GitHub API.
- `commit.rs`: Atomic multi-file commits (Git Tree/Blob push).
- `auth.rs`: OAuth PKCE flow implementation.

### `wiki`
- `parser.rs`: Pulldown-cmark + frontmatter extraction.
- `linker.rs`: Regex-based wiki-link resolution.

### `memvid`
- `session_recorder.rs`: Hooks into `core` to record events into `MV2` format.

